<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12053q"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12053q">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12053q"> 53(q)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> l&apos;id&eacute;l n&apos;a qu&apos;un temps</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les personnes qui descendent de l&apos;abbaye sont plus impatientes encore que les nouveaux arriv&eacute;s. Elles viennent de promener sous les vo&ucirc;tes du clo&icirc;tre leurs r&ecirc;ves romantiques; elles ont &eacute;voqu&eacute; l&apos;histoire des temps anciens et leurs &acirc;mes ont pris leur essor du haut des plates-formes a&eacute;riennes, au del&agrave; de l&apos;escalier de dentelle; mais <mark>l&apos;id&eacute;al n&apos;a qu&apos;un temps</mark>; les jambes sont bris&eacute;es, les yeux clignotent, fatigu&eacute;s d&apos;avoir trop contempl&eacute;; le cerveau est lourd, l&apos;estomac creux et les touristes abandonnent enfin les sommets de l&apos;art pour les r&eacute;alit&eacute;s de la vie. <br><font color="green">[People who come down from the abbey are even more impatient than the newly arrived. They have enjoyed their romantic dreams under the vaults of the cloister; they have evoked the old history and their souls have soared above the high aerial platforms, above &ldquo;the stair of lace&rdquo;; but <mark>the ideal lasts only for a time</mark>; the legs are tired, the eyes are weary, tired of taking in too much; the brains are heavy, the stomach empty and in the end the tourists abandon the summits of art for the realities of life.]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="SMIN" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SMIN"><cite title="source">Le Mont Saint-Michel Inconnu</cite></a> (1912) 68</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
